caption: After lunch at Wurstkuche, we decided to walk over to Little Tokyo to grab some mochi ice cream.  I've been to Little Tokyo before, but I have never tried this place.  I guess they supply the mochi ice cream that is available in the freezer section of Trader Joe's.

I just came here last tonight with my boyfriend and friends. The worker was kind and patience with us since it was our first time here. She let us sample a bunch of flavors and even gave us recommendations on what's popular. The Creamy …
I ended up going with a Kid's Scoop of the Hollywood Rock Cafe, though it was such a hard decision for me. I thoroughly enjoyed the entire scoop and wanted to get more after I finished it haha.
There's better ice cream out there. Sure they have unique flavors but it wasn't "omg so good, I would totally drive out to Hollywood Rock Cafe just for ice cream" good.
Awesome atmosphere and super amiable service. The food was crisp and yummy. Will surely recommend this place to my friends. Fair prices and big meals. Great work.

Walked by this historical beaut while galavanting across the city, we stopped in for ice cream and ordered a smidge in a waffle cone, me with mint chip and him the peanut butter thing. I really liked that I could taste the fresh mint, and …

- Vanilla Ice Cream - I was in the area, and saw this cute ice cream shop. So I decided to try it. The vanilla tasted very flavorful, just like the vanilla bean. The texture was not icy, rather it was smooth and substantial. I dislike it when ice cream is more icy and watery, but all the samples here were good.

I came here awhile ago with my boyfriend. The food is amazing! They make some really tasty sandwiches and delectable sweets. The store even has a cute whimsical look to it. The only downfall is that parking can be hard to find and it can get pricey.

They have vegan options and it was honestly the best vegan ice cream I have ever had! Note that I rarely give 5 Stars, so you know I was pleased!  I loved the Elvis Presley vegan ice cream, which is banana, peanut butter, and jelly! BTW, …

Might be kinda basic of me to admit this, but this place is probably one of my favorite ice cream places in LA. The flavors available are pretty unique and interesting, I wish I could try everything! Most recently I got the Twenty-Four Blackbirds' Matcha Mint Truffle and the Chocolate Gooey Brownie. Both were delicious!
Got the secret breakfast. Boozey bourbon base with nice big chunks of salted cereal studded throughout. My favorite ice cream in all of SF.
Friendly service and very good, flavorful ice cream. I especially liked the secret breakfast and the cinnamon  tres leches.

It's never a bad experience here. The employees are so kind to help you make the perfect Ice cream decisions. Every time I drop by for a scoop of ice cream, I really have to grab a pint for the house.

This place is really good and the staff was very friendly. I can tell the meat on philly steak sandwich is much better quality than other places I've tried. The restaurant is clean, price is reasonable and food is good. What more can you ask for?

I LOVE YOLO!!! My family and I go here almost everyday to get bubble tea!! I have also tried some of the food and the smoothies and everything is always so good! The customer service is always fast and very friendly. Try the Yolo Cobb salad or Thai tea with bobba. Delicious!

Absolutely best ice cream and shakes in the city. Very reasonable prices. All homemade, organic ingredients. Unique flavors and new twists on old favorites. Employees are polite and patient. They will help you with any questions. Truly one of a kind.

Hands down, probably one of the best ice cream places in CA! We got the flight with mint chocolate chip, strawberry balsamic, Chocoberry cheesecake, French roasted coffee, and honey mango sorbet. We literally couldn't pick a favorite because they were all soooooo good. Come here! You won't be disappointed.

Sam's friend ice cream is absolutely amazing. My favorite is the fried red velvet Oreos. They are to die for  and the price for it is pretty decent if you ask me. They were 6 Oreos for 4 dollars. My friend always gets the coconut ice cream with the cornflake crust. He is obsessed with it. Will always come back for more.
Cornflakes crumb coat it for sure!  Service is excellent! Very courteous and easy going staff! Not a long wait being that it is fried and also a 70+ degree weather.
Their vegan flavors are amazing ! Could not even tell they were Vegan ! Cute little shop as well with very friendly staff.
Love love!  They have a vegan lavender variety that I don't mind driving the distance for.  Charming neighborhood spot.

I love coming here! They always have very unique delicious flavors of ice cream! It's super cute and clean inside too, workers are always very friendly and they let you sample unlimited amounts of ice cream. The ice cream comes here are …

A small selection of unique flavors.  Your options are comprised of Hometown Creamery year-round staples and seasonal flavors that rotate.  I had the key lime pie which was delicious!  The homemade waffle cone makes it even better.
Wishing the Decorations of the ice cream was prettier but taste trumps decor any day. Prices are cool and it's surrounded by decent restaurants for this to be your after meal snack.

Superior ice cream. Always a new flavor of the month. Love the waffles. They taste just as good as they smell when they are baking. Sweet staff. Very small, but very clean. Always busy no matter what time of the year. So happy we stumbled in one day.
Ice cream and hip hop at its best. Leave with a sweet filling of ice cream. A must go for not only the ice cream but the full experience.
Mikey is an awesome and exceptional crafter of ice cream. The Pink Floyd was impeccable and nothing like I've ever had before. Will be going again next time I'm in Los Angeles.

A CA favorite. When I got off the airplane I drove straight to Hollywood Rock Cafe for Secret Breakfast (bourbon and corn flakes ice cream). Every other flavor is delicious, but Secret Breakfast is the flavor that I typically order. The …
There large ice cream selection was so flavorful and creamy. Just so happened to stumble upon this gem. Will definitely going back when in town.

One of THE best ice cream places I've been to! The Secret Breakfast flavor is a must try. If you're going to with two or more people, consider getting a pint from the fridge to skip the usually long lines.

I love coming here when in CA. They have the most creative flavors. We got the beet was delicious but I always end up having the "secret breakfast" it's so darn good with that hint of bourbon. Always friendly  workers and love the benches outside to sit and lick away!
Best ice cream I've ever had! And all of their flavors are so unique. You can split a one scoop serving between two flavors. I picked salted caramel cocoa nib and Harvey milk & honey graham.

Love the unique flavors - excited to find a seasonal pumpkin with white chocolate pretzels! Also had a scoop of the golden milk with gingersnap (cold use more snap). Woman working was not friendly and could hardly manage to utter a few words of acknowledgment.

Went here for some late night dessert, solid recommendation from a friend! They have a lot of eclectic flavors. It reminds me of flavors available at some of the ice cream shops we'd visited in Japan. The ice cream itself was pretty good, price was decent.

Always a great place to stop in for a snack but as I said if you don't want to wait he longgg line go to the soft serve window. The selection is much smaller but on a hot SF day either is worth the wait.
Hip place, hip crowd, good ice cream....

Oh my sinful sweet tooth! This is the most yummiest frozen custard I've ever had the pleasure of self indulging.... You can add so many different toppings, not just on top, but right in middle, like a hurricane of blissful satisfaction. Please try this incredible frozen custard whenever possible! You will not regret it!!!!

Love this little place . I've been coming here since I was a kid . The old style drive up with car service is pretty call . The ice cream shakes and sundaes are quite tasty but my favorite thing to get here would be the corn dog and fries . This is a fun little place to take the kids of a afternoon treat .
It's ice cream and sorbets, can't really go wrong with that. Friendly staff and the portions are big for the price. Would recommend for a cool snack.

Whenever I eat food in Koreatown, I always end up grabbing dessert here. They sell a variety of drinks and desserts here. Their Thai tea is great and I love their ice cream macaron sandwiches! I've even bought their Snow Monster beanie because of how much I love their stuff  Would 100% recommend to anyone with a dessert craving.

Coffee toffee ice cream sandwich, meh. Maybe it was the heat. Maybe I was crabby but it just didn't seem worth the wait to me. Labor day was a spectacle. DIRTY tables. No sort of variety. I didn't enjoy and I wasn't pleased.

It's not worth the hype in my opinion. The macaroon sandwich was too sweet- I ordered Thai Tea. After eating half of it, I was ready to throw it away or give it to someone. The milkshake took forever! It was also too sweet and nothing worth …

Yes! Yes! You can't go wrong going to this place. Once you taste their ice cream macaroons, don't forget to get a blondie or a brownie or a cupcake. Everything is just delicious! The crew is so chill and groovy.
Was in Sf for the weekend so you know I had to find a good icecream combo here. This time it was roasted banana and cookies and cream. Soo goood.

People complain that it's over priced...blah blah...go to rite aid... You are paying for quality. Hence why there is always a line, I come to milk at least every other week because I live so close. I've tried almost everything...have yet …

For all you dessert lovers out there...have you ever secretly wondered what would happen if a macaroon and ice cream hooked up and had a baby? Wonder no more! I had a thai tea macaroon ice cream sandwich and it was phenomenal. I was worried …

Pretty sure when I came here, I got two in the same day - I just couldn't resist. Both the cookies and cream and red velvet were on point, and nothing I've tried since I've visited Hollywood Rock Cafe has lived up to the amazingness I experienced that day. Line or not, I'm coming back for you, Hollywood Rock Cafe.
Great service
Best ice cream in Los Angeles.  This place is clean, bright, and full of fun flavors.  Love the window looking into the kitchen!!!

I love love love that they go sorbet heavy here because a good sorbet is hard to find. The ramune sorbet here is heavenly. So light and citrusy. The rest of the flavors are incredible too, so imaginative and well executed. I'm a sucker for weird flavors and this place definitely doesn't disappoint!
Amazing smoothies and friendly staff.
This place has such a lovely and attentive staff as well as some seriously ass-kicking smoothies! Will definitely be visiting again :)
They have the amazing coffee I have ever had 😍 and they all so sweet
GREAT place. Food is good and the owner is SO SWEET!!! Highly recommend!!!
The owner is so sweet! The food was delicious and prepared fresh when we ordered. Next time I come to LA I'll be sure to come back!

It is one of the few places where you can have organic smoothies and organic tea. If you are visiting LA in summer this place can be savior.

Everything from the taste and quality of product to the phenomenal customer service great place.

Delicious Organic fruit smoothies ... Great customer service as well!  If you are strolling down Hollywood Blvd, this is well worth the stop!    Alex, we will definitely make a point of stopping here the next time we are in LA -- enjoyed chatting with you so much!         Terry & DeWayne
I come here all the time, the smoothies are the tastiest in town and the staff and owner are super friendly!

Great yogurt place! I like the vibe and atmosphere. The employees are friendly and have great customer service. My friend got the organic strawberry banana smoothie and she loved it. They have outside seating directly on hollywood blvd.
